Phase 8: Validate the Forecast
Purpose

Confirm whether the model is useful before giving it to managers.

Validation process
Choose a past week.
Pretend you did not know the actual sales.
Run the model using only data before that week.
Compare forecast vs actual sales.
Measure error percentage.
Accuracy formula
Error % = ABS(Actual - Forecast) / Actual × 100
Example
Date	Store	Forecast	Actual	Error
2026-03-12	101	$2,500	$2,600	3.85%
2026-03-13	101	$2,700	$2,550	5.88%
Target

For phase one, aim to see whether the model is consistently better than manual forecasting.

